THE FIX UNDER TEST
  In routes.rs B4 capture block, after kv::read_global_k fills the live gk and before
  pushing the Episode: scale the live gk in place so its mean per-vector L2 norm
  (over ng*npos HD=512 vectors) matches the curated registry's mean per-vector L2 norm.
  Logged as "B4-NIGHTSHIFT: K-norm calib live=.. curated=.. scale=..".

MEASURED K-NORMS (constant every capture)
  live_mean_norm   = 1.415
  curated_mean_norm= 2.774
  scale            = 2.774 / 1.415 = 1.9605

  >>> DIAGNOSIS WAS INVERTED. The live gk per-vector norm (1.415) is SMALLER than the
      curated/trained distribution (2.774), NOT larger. The calibration therefore scales
      the live K UP by 1.96x, not down. (The "live K-norm super-attractor / live > curated"
      framing in the bug ticket does not hold against the substrate.)

