VERDICT: HONEST NEGATIVE — calibration did NOT restore foreign-reject.
  T1 PASS (consolidated + calib logged). T2 PASS (matched live wins, 41.294). T3 FAIL
  (foreign still recalls ep_live_000 at 42.588 — even slightly HIGHER than the matched T2).

WHY THE UNIFORM K-NORM SCALE DOES NOT FIX IT (structural, not a magnitude offset)
  1. The live wc_score is ~constant (T2 41.294 vs T3 42.588) and query-INDEPENDENT, and the
     foreign turn scores HIGHER. A single global K magnitude is NOT what makes the live
     episode super-attract — so matching the mean per-vector norm cannot remove it.
  2. wc_score = logsumexp-over-positions then mean-over-heads of the W_c-projected q.K.
     logsumexp_p(s * x_p) != s * logsumexp_p(x_p): a constant K scale s sharpens/saturates the
     position-softmax, it does NOT linearly rescale the score, so "match the mean norm" has no
     clean lever on the final number.
  3. The whole curated panel swings turn-to-turn (T2 all positive ~[-7,+8]; T3 all NEGATIVE
     ~[-24,-4]) while the live episode stays pinned ~+42. The live K from the scratch-prefill
     read_global_k has a different per-position / per-head DISTRIBUTIONAL SHAPE than the
     curated ep.k the head trained on (the live capture lacks the curator pipeline's
     normalization / position structure). Mean-per-vector-norm is too coarse a statistic to
     reconcile that shape difference.

DEEPER CAUSE / NEXT LEVERS (for B4-v2, not shipped here)
  - The live/curated K difference is STRUCTURAL (per-position + per-head distribution), not a
    uniform scale. Candidate fixes: (a) per-(head)-channel or per-position norm calibration,
    or whitening to the curated K covariance, rather than one scalar; (b) capture the live
    episode through the SAME curator path (test_gemma4_ppl_cuda SP_XBAR_RECALL_WRITE /
    sp_xbar_manifest_serialize) that produced the trained ep.k, so provenance matches by
    construction; (c) the documented B4-v2 admission gate (teacher-forced ablation oracle,
    collapse < TAU=-8) would reject the foreign capture's recall regardless of score shape.
  - Also confirmed: T2 and T3 each self-capture as ep_live_001 / ep_live_002 (no admission
    gate yet) — the documented B4-v2 TODO.

